sentence: Joe Simon (born September 2, 1943) is an American soul and R&B musician.
He began as a Gospel artist singing with the Golden West Singers in the Bay Area in California.

A consistent presence on the US charts between 1964 and 1981, Simon charted 51 U.S. Pop and R&B chart hits between 1964 and 1981, including eight times in the US top forty, thirty-eight times in the top 40 of the US R&B charts, and 13 chart hits in Canada.
